The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 30: Mukesh Ambani-run Reliance Industries has bought back US energy giant Chevron Corps 5 per cent stake in Reliance Petroleum for Rs 1,350 crore. In a disclosure to the Bombay Stock Exchange, Reliance Petroleum (RPL) said Chevron India Holdings has sold 22.50 crore shares, representing a 5 per cent stake in RPL, to Reliance Industries.                             
	 New Delhi, April 30: The new pension scheme for all citizens will be open from tomorrow, the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority said. This follows a clearance by the Election Commission, which had earlier stalled the scheme.                             
	 Mumbai, April 30: Jet Airways has decided to terminate the contracts of some employees who have superannuated as a measure to cut cost. Sources said contracts of 50 employees were due for renewal, which eventually got scrapped.                            
	 Calcutta, April 30: Harsh Vardhan Lodha, the younger son of late Rajendra Singh Lodha, has moved a petition before Calcutta High Court seeking an order to appoint him as an administrator of the Rs 5000-crore asset and properties of late Priyamvada Birla.                            
	 Mumbai, April 30: Asset management company DSP BlackRock Investment Managers has decided to close a part of its portfolio management services business in India by the end of June.                                                                                                                           
